==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Danaide
<hw>Da"na*ide</hw> <pr>(d⟦amac⟧"n⟦adot⟧*⟦imac⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From the mythical <ets>Danaides</ets>, who were condemned to fill
with water a vessel full of holes.]</ety> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A
water wheel having a vertical axis, and an inner and outer tapering
shell, between which are vanes or floats attached usually to both
shells, but sometimes only to one.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Danaite</ent>⟦br⟧
